@ericrbg Thanks for the suggestion!
Using namespace looks like a good suggestion, I'll adopt it in the next commit.

`Greedoid` will have its own type, as shown in the [working branch](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/9a42ee5c3eca67135fc38906c9f9b3d32daebc5e/Mathlib/Data/Greedoid/Basic.lean#L176-L180). It was also in the file `Basic.lean`, but I received a suggestion to add the file in the next contributing push. To summarize, the `Greedoid` structure will be there, but not now.
